Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards in the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance is forbidden
In the context of the tragic crash of the Student Agency bus near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can travel within the bus during the journey.
"If the law was to be strictly and formally respected, the activity of a steward is contrary to the traffic law," said the spokesman for the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the way to the coach.
The girl was at that moment unfortunately sitting next to the driver, on the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she had two other seats at her disposal.
However, the coach may have an accident or even a sudden brake, also when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the bus is equipped with standing or not.
If this standing equipment is not approved, passengers shall remain seated.
The Student Agency long distance buses do not have standing places; this was confirmed in Aktuálně.cz by the director of Radim Jančura.
"This is a matter that we dealt with with the department and, at first, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got the passengers to go to the toilet during the trip provided they had their own seat," he revealed his position.
The law ignores the steward
"There is no unequivocal legal interpretation of the steward's role - there is no legal prescription for this role.
On the other hand, there is no legal requirement to prohibit the carrier from offering services.
The law on road transport knows only the term "vehicle receiver"; it does not define its rights and duties," adds spokesman Hanzelka more ambiguously.
Josef Pokorný, the head of the road traffic department, believes, on the contrary, that the law sufficiently addresses the problem.
"It depends on the fact that the coach has permission in its approval to offer standing places.
Everything is in there," he says.
Buses are divided into urban areas, where there are standing places and a limited maximum speed, inter-urban areas with standing places and a higher authorized speed and long-distance buses without standing places with the highest maximum permitted speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
As on the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Ho+n, expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"In regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
There, too, it is not sure when turbulence will occur and the stewardess of the air can hit her head."
"Now, in the event that the coach would have braked abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards by internal requirements," he said and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not solved.
Jančura is ready to abolish these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer steward services.
He's hiring two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their job to be a risky job.
"Nevertheless, as soon as I feel that this is a risky job, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and diary when boarding.
It would also reduce costs," he said.
The safety concern is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of the Asiana Alexey Litvine, who ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses. We've been opposing them from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end in a fatal accident," he said a year ago in Týden.cz.
A huge tragedy has happened
A young hostess from the Plze+ region, who had been working for the company for two years, died during the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop strip without using a blinker and it blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he approached him by his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards have been sold.
"In the case of long distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the judgment of the court, but as far as financial compensation is concerned, it also relies on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been being drafted for more than a year by a group of 30 experts from the Ministry of Transport, could clarify the travel of stewards on board the coach.
"However, it did not reach any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the motorway and the use of the mobile phone at the wheel," says the expert Ho+n.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of stewards as something that would fundamentally endanger the safety of passengers," concludes spokesman Hanzelka, stating that the control of the safety of coaches is under the power of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
